The `IsSome` inductive type only has one constructor `of_some` which applies to `some a`, not to `none`. So if we assume `IsSome none`, we can derive a contradiction by pattern matching on it (since no constructor can produce `IsSome none`).

In Lean 4, I can use `intro h` to assume `IsSome none`, then use `cases h` or `nomatch h` to derive a contradiction, or simply use `fun h => nomatch h`.

